  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Punch down bao buns and let them rise for 30 minutes.",
    "Mix mentaiko, unsalted butter, heavy cream, Gruyere cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg, salt, and black pepper in a bowl until smooth.",
    "Place bao buns on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and spoon the mentaiko mixture evenly into each bun.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for 5 minutes before serving."
